From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Thu, 4 Dec 2025 15:43:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: cix: card-utils: Default clock provider when not
 specified in DT

When no frame-master/bitclock-master is specified in the device tree,
the clock provider mask remains unset (0), causing I2S drivers to reject
the format with EINVAL.

The vendor kernel's snd_soc_of_parse_daifmt() uses
snd_soc_daifmt_clock_provider_from_bitmap() which returns
SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBC_CFC as the default when neither master is specified.

The mainline card-utils.c uses separate parsing functions
(snd_soc_daifmt_parse_format + snd_soc_daifmt_parse_clock_provider_as_phandle)
which don't set a default.

Add the same default behavior: when no clock master phandles are present,
default to SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBC_CFC (codec consumes clocks = CPU provides).

This fixes the following error during sound card registration:
  cdns-i2s-mc 7070000.i2s: ASoC error (-22): at snd_soc_dai_set_fmt()

Baseline commit before DMA-350 cyclic implementation work.
---
 sound/soc/cix/card-utils.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/cix/card-utils.c b/sound/soc/cix/card-utils.c
index 6296584b6ff2e..f349edad35d83 100644
--- a/sound/soc/cix/card-utils.c
+++ b/sound/soc/cix/card-utils.c
@@ -88,6 +88,13 @@ static int cix_dailink_parsing_fmt(struct device_node *np,
 			dai_fmt |= SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBP_CFP;
 		else
 			dai_fmt |= SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBC_CFC;
+	} else {
+		/*
+		 * No clock master specified - default to codec as consumer
+		 * (CPU/I2S provides clocks). This matches vendor kernel
+		 * behavior from snd_soc_daifmt_clock_provider_from_bitmap(0).
+		 */
+		dai_fmt |= SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CBC_CFC;
 	}
 	of_node_put(bitclkmaster);
 	of_node_put(framemaster);
